main event: A commercial airline pilot observed an object flying towards Albuquerque from Deming, New Mexico.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at 25,000 feet and seemed to be moving very fast.,The observation lasted approximately 15 seconds.,The object had a slight light and emitted no visible tail light.,The report was received as a CIRVIS (Civilian Report of Unidentified Sightings) report.,It was suggested that the observer probably saw a jet aircraft based on the altitude and flight path.
